Would surely recommend eating here. Exceptional mood, delightful food, fantastic service. 5 stars.
You won't regret trying this spot. He arrives at around. Worth the wait and long line. He's very nice and fast. Don Chingon on a bowl or on the stick.

Our new fave neighborhood spot. Food was so so good. Fresh, delicious, plentiful. And equally as important, the staff was so accommodating and nice. It was stop and start rain while we were sitting outside and they were quick to get us shelter and reset up for us when it stopped. Also, amazing drinks. Spicy mezcal margarita was 100%!!!

We love the food and atmosphere at this restaurant. The staff are always friendly and helpful even when they are busy with Barclay's Center crowds. We love the Carnitas and Carne Asada tacos as well as the chicken burrito, very filling and yummy. If we're really hungry the guacamole to start is fantastic as is the brooklyn queso.
Would absolutely recommend visiting this place. Fantastic vibes, tasty food, excellent customer service. 5 stars.
Healthy serving and good food
The food and service was excellent. The ambiance is subtle and welcoming. I'd definitely recommend this place to folks to try out.

The Authentic taste was amazing. The Bartender Jose was awesome his drinks were made with the knowledge and skill of the Mexican tradition and taste. The place is a must if you love real Hispanic culture and taste.Each cuisen was filled with tantalizing spices I thought had been Americanized but not here true Mexican flavor.

We went to eat before a concert. Definitely centrally located. The guacamole was amazing. The chicken tacos were delicious the carnitas were so so.  The drinks were delicious and not watery. The place is nothing fancy but a small hidden gem.

Aside from having a funny name, this place makes some legit food and their tacos and margaritas are absolutely Delicious. Came here on a first date and I think we had six margaritas each. No over the top flavors, just authentic mixes. Everyone should stop in if you're looking for a quick bite.
Service and Serving Sizes were amazing. Convenient right off Bergen 2/3 train stop. Gluten free options and a dope atmosphere.
Great and fresh food, I like the ambience this spot has, and the employees were very friendly. I will definitely eat here again.
Great taco and brittos!!! Nice waiters!
Great drinks

Outstanding food and service! Brooklyn Queso is on point, and the Chicken Burrito is so well prepared and comes with great sides!! Every meal has been fantastic, and the bar staff is awesome. Margaritas are incredible too!
Always a local fav. Great staff and delicious food and margs!
Tasty taco / Mexican restaurant. We got the 3 taco combos. Both were excellent and plenty of food for a reasonable price. Smaller restaurant, but doesn't feel cramped at all.
(Translated by Google) Good food and good margaritas! Nice place  (Original) Buena comida y buenas margaritas! Lindo lugar
Went here with my ex and boy it was delish!!! Very affordable pricing also. ❤️ 😋
Great tacos!
We sat at the bar, had some really good tacos served with delicious garlic rice. The bartender was really nice. The atmosphere was really chill. The drinks were really delicious. Really.

Great food, excellent portions. I had the crispy pork tacos and my hubby had the steak quesadilla. Both were delicious with tender meat with great flavor. Loves the rice and beans. Margaritas were perfect as well! Perfect for pregaming before a Barclays event.
Good food good service :)

We love hanging out. Last night we arrived in this fine place which we didn’t know before. We had a lovely time there with delicious meal and a well-trained crew and a distinguished cook. We  added this place in our phone list  and we will surely come back very soon. We warmly recommend.
Love this place . I recommend
Food was delicious!

The food and the drinks are so good here.  I dream about the dulce y caliente margaritas.. the carnitas tacos are out of this world... The elotes appetizer is a little slice of heaven.  I've never had a bad dish or a bad drink here.. I recommend whole heartedly!
Excellent food. Good service. Cozy atmosphere.

I went around 430/5pm. There wasn't a wait, nor was it packed. We sat at the bar since seating options weren't the best. Food was ok. We had chips with queso, but the queso tasted chalky to me. Maybe they incorporate powdered cheese? But I loved the peppers and not so spicey pickled jalapenos. Drinks were also ok. Nothing to special. Just a good place with great open windows to have some Mexican food.

Great authentic food, service, and the ambience is relaxing. I would love to give it a four or five star rating but cannot. Due to the fact there have been no changes to enhance the experience at this location. I’ve been going here on many occasions for more than two years. There are many other restaurants in the area enhancing the customers experience besides this one. No Taco Tuesdays which it odd since almost every other Mexican restaurant in Brooklyn and New York City areas have made this a trending theme - it’s even promoted domestically on social media outlets.  I don’t normally write reviews and if I do it’s because I really like or extremely dislike the business and need others to get a genuine and unbiased opinion. I am hoping the owner sees this to at least try and make improvements. Other than my respectful rant, there are great workers and cooks who always do their best with what they have to accommodate, and that’s what keeps me coming back (besides the food of course!)😆
Really great happy hour!
Very cute small place. But nice. Food was good.

Amazing

Nice ambience shabby but chic, However the food was uninspiring  it did not taste very authentic However the presentation was nice I suppose if you’re looking for fast and efficient this will be a place to go there are just too many options out there At this particular price point for me to go again
Small restuarant and boring menu not much of a food selection to choose from. Had to sit sit facing a wall at a small table attached to the wall with my back to the whole restuarant.
Solid Mexican spot
Great place. Tasty cozy and awsome.

Bomb taco shop near prospect Park!! Got carnitas plate, and the Brooklyn queso dip... Tacos were well made, meat flavorful, and the dip was divine. Romantic setting for a taco shop! Plus, best house tequilla I have ever tasted, tried it at Omar's recommendation, it was superb! Great experience, would recommend 10/10
Great food! Cool vibe!

Real good food and service.  Will go back!

Really nice fullfilling food - big portions fresh ingredients. I tried the fish tacos, avocado tacos and the pollo - they were perfect each dish comes with rice and beans - the chips that came with the guac were freshly baked and the guac had a new ingredeint I never tried before; green grapes. Overall really delicious food.
Pretty good drink special

Great spot to hit up before you go to the Barclay. Went here on a whim. Glad I did. The food was great, the tacos 🌮 were stuffed with goodness. The ambience is sheek, with a great table top looking out to the street. The rice and beans were awesome, the rice had a buttery taste to it, which no one does and I loved it. Their strong point is the food, the margarita was weak. My only concern is that happy hour ends at 6, it should be 4-8. Many nyc people don't get out until 6 anyways, like myself. The service was prompt, my waitress was kind and patient.
Food was amazing went there for my birthday, cinco de mayo.. Unlimited margaritas for an hour! 😁😁
Delicious one word
Service was awesome. You get a lot of food. But it's not a place I'd travel for
Truly authentic Mexican food. We ordered the tacos and the burrito - will definitely be back!
We've ordered burritos and they were awesome. Huge portions. Waiters were polite, funny and helpful. I will come back for sure.
Slamming margaritas and the guacamole was right up my alley too!

The food was seasoned just perfect.. I had the chicken quesadilla.. My partner had the fish burrito... Cooked to perfection! Jose was our server also bartender (we sat at the bar) cozy pl2cae comfortable.. And will be back.. Rv with sports on ans music playing in the background.. Right across from Barclays Center.

Everything we have tried has been awesome! Not our normal neighborhood, but our dog is being treated at a vet nearby so we were looking for lunch  to break the stress of sitting at the vet. We went in with no expectations, but came out with a belly of praise! Watching the cooks make the corn tortillas on the spot was a treat. Go here, you will love it.

small but good eats. nice drinks and vibe

Hands down the best Mexican food I’ve tasted in a long time! I live in Long Island so there isn’t many to choose from! If you ever are in the area or have a concert at the Barclays center this is the place to go! The service was fast the prices were really good for the quality of food I wish it was a little bit bigger we had to sit by the window so while you were stuffing your face people would constantly look at you but no big deal definitely not a deal breaker! My cousin and I attended the post Malone concert and wanted to eat something before I’m glad we chose this place we ordered the Brooklyn queso amazing we ordered two orders of the jalapeño poppers they were so good lightly fried so it wasn’t heavy on the stomach, elote with was probably the best I’ve ever eaten and then the chicken quesadilla omg so good! Along with two drinks total 60 dollars! Can’t beat that
The food is amazing, especially the guacamole and jalapeno poppers. Staff is friendly - Jose is great. I’ve never had a bad experience here.
Consistently delicious, I think they put crack in the pork right before they perfectly sear it. The place is always spotless and smells amazing when you walk in.
Great place, great food. Nice atmosphere

Wow! Visited last night and everything on my plate was delicious! I ordered the carnitas quesadilla, which was accompanied by salsa, guacamole, sour cream, rice, and refried beans. Quite a bit of food for just the right price. I was surprised to find out that a coke was billed @ $5, and there was a $5 fee added on for sitting at the bar. Nevertheless, the food was amazing so I’ll let the fee and the coke slide 😏

It can be a good hangout spot on a nice day.

One of our absolute favorites in Brooklyn. Great selection of drinks and the food is always fresh and tasty. We've never had a bad meal here! Love their fresh take on guac with grapes and pomegranate seeds, and the jalapeno poppers are a delicious shareable appetizer. Staff is very friendly.

Fantastic cocktails and food. Fast and very friendly service. The menu is concentrated on a few things done really well (fish tacos and steak burrito are amazing). Broad selection of top shelf tequila and añejo. My favorite Mexican place in the city.

Great and attentive service from the get go. Food is solid (chorizo quesadilla) and hit the spot for me. Their dishes look well put together, not just thrown on a plate as with other places.
